<br />

<br />
For my part, I would find the <i>horrific nerf</i> of our solo abilities took in OoW more tolerarble if Sony hadn't been slowly eroding our group desirability for years now.  At it stands now, unless you are in <i>one of two zones in the game</i> (Vxed or Tipt), enchanters are purely and <i>massively</i> inferior to bards, and frequently significantly inferior to shamans and beastlords.  The growing irrelevance of mez compared to the Sony's apparent facination with increasingly more powerful pulling tools (bards got too good at pulling, so the solution was to... give monks unresistable lull?), combined with the active intention of designing zones that are easily and quickly pulled (from BoT all the way to MPG, it's a far cry from SolB or Sebilis.  A brain damaged chimp can pull singles in MPG all day long), has turned enchanters into the buff bots we always feared we'd someday be.
<br />

<br />
I can live, unhappily, with going from a class that can get credible solo XP (though not as much as druids, wizards, necros) to a class that bascially has to group if they want to advance.  However, I am very unhappy, and considering simply canceling my account, if I am to be a class that cannot solo effectively <i>and</i> who's core class abilities are being steadily devalued.  Unmei is simply and totally correct.  Any other class in the game gets significant upgrades from OoW; enchanters get, in many ways, <span style="font-style: italic">less</span> powerful.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=530073" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ianthe Dawnglory</a>
<br />
Enchanter
<br />
Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
