                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The irony of this situation is i personally don't think there is any "old" code that makes anything level 65+ uncharmable.
<br />

<br />
If you want to flag a mob uncharmable then you get the message "this mob cannot be charmed". Currently its just an automatic resist.
<br />

<br />
As for testing old content - none was done. None could be done as they closed off all the non-OoW zones during beta. Although this was partially due to folk going exploring with /betabuff when their mains couldn't access the zones.
<br />

<br />
The major reason charm has been nerfed (cough *changed*) again and again is because folk see it as an easy way to get exp. They complain about it and eventually someone get out the sledge hammer and wacks the problem. All they needed was piece of wire wool.
<br />
Of course the real solo'ists have never been affected by this and still aren't.
<br />

<br />
So my best guess to this serverwide flag is that it is yet another *change* to stop us soloing places like PoFire, as it would be to unbalancing for raid content and exp.
<br />

<br />
But the real solo'ists can still solo everywhere, the difference - the only major difference - is that they couldn't use their kite tactics against existing content.
<br />

<br />
(yeah charming can be risky as heck but the only time folk really see it is at the hands of someone that is well practiced - we make it look to easy)
<br />

<br />
Can't really call it a "knee-jerk" reaction when the sledge just obliterated half the leg, can we?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
