                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This one time at a group that I was with gathered around to watch a light show. The stars were out and we were in a remote location. Some meteors were streaming down and the moon was slowly rising on the horizon. We looked with binoculars and telescopes at the amazing ritual of time unfolding before us in the timeless wonder of the starfilled sky. Soon we all began to gather in the toolshed and huddled closely together in a spectator fashion. The children all were in the front and the adults stood with nodded approval behind them. As the single light bulb was shut off we all were witness to the second light show of the evening. The CD burned and sparkled as the Teslacoil zapped its mettallic content right off the acrylic disc. The children were all in agast as the plasma rays changed colors and the smell of burned oxide was in the air. Soon the Teslacoil had finished its merciful act of ridding us of yet another SOE product. The Expansion CD was now powerless, now rid of any semblance of digital coding. It had given it's last light show in our little house on the prairie. Merry Christmas to us and to SOE goodnight.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/eusa_drool.gif" alt="eusa_drool.gif" border="0" /> <span style="color: violet"></span></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Chicks Rule, Boys Drool <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
